QUALIFICATIONS

Deliv

Join us in disrupting logistics and setting the new standard for last mile delivery, a multibillion dollar market. We are a b2b service, behind the scenes of 4000+ national omni-channel retailers, e-commerce players and businesses (i.e. Best Buy, Walgreens, Kohl’s, Williams-Sonoma, Google Shopping Express), transforming how goods move around a city. Deliv has raised $40 million, including our recent $28M B-round, and is backed by global logistics leader UPS, leading Venture Capital investors including Upfront Ventures and RPM Ventures, and the nation’s top REIT investors.

About The Opportunity

Deliv is seeking multiple full-stack engineers to expand our team of engineers. This role will involve back-end, front-end and some mobile work, so you should be strong at at least two of them, and willing/interested to learn in the third. We have a culture of “move fast, and try not to break too many things.”

We’re looking to fill lead software engineer position from Turkey working remotely with flexible work hours. This person will be leading the team that we want to build in Turkey.

What You'll Do

• Develop new features across our full stack (Rails, React, Python) and our iOS/Android apps (Objective-C, and Java).

• Back up features with corresponding tests (we like tests, on all the platforms!).
• Design, build and scale our web and mobile applications to be fast and reliable.
• Participate in discussions with operations and product for planning what gets built. 

• Have a voice on architecture, implementation, and engineering process.

You Are

Your experience may span one year or multiple decades, but you are a true “full-stack” engineer. React or mobile may be new to you, but you're proficient with similar technologies and you're excited to learn.

•Ready to shake things up in a stodgy mature industry while using some very cool technology.

• Passionate about e-commerce, crowd-sourcing, and/or RESTful APIs.

• Fascinated by geolocation data, vehicle routing problems, traveling salesman problems, or figuring out how do we get that delivery from here to there efficiently.

• A real teammate. Culture is critical here. We’ve all got a million things to do, and you’re happy to chip in wherever you can to help your teammates out when they’re underwater.

• Someone who recognizes the art of engineering. We like writing tests, CI, and love code quality metrics. Code reviews are awesome, and you’re always looking forward to learning something new.

• Someone who’s comfortable working quickly, with lots of iterations, and shipping often.

What You'll Need

  • 5+ years of experience in software engineering

  • Experience with REST APIs—you should know the REST basics inside and out.

  • Familiar with the git workflow.

  • 3+ Production experience with a back-end language like Java, C, or C++

  • Excellent communication skills in English.

  • Flexibility to attend off-hour meetings due to time zone difference.

Bonus Points

• Production experience with a scripting language like Python or Ruby.

• Experience building native IOS or Android applications. Personal projects count.

• Devops skills using Amazon AWS services.

• Experience scaling a Ruby on Rails platform to handle high volume.

• Proficient in SQL, NoSQL (and know when is the right time for which), as well as other data stores (redis, memcached, etc).

• Open-source projects on github.
• Experience with location-based applications. 

• Experience with R or machine learning.
